<HEAD>WASHINGTON: follow-up, yes.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Q. Please. You want to be sure that your seven granddaughters
have the same opportunities that your pride and joy, George P., has.
George P. is one whom you take on fishing trips, into the back rooms
with the boys, and to the research camp at the University of
Nebraska and things like that. I wonder if you're planning to take
some of the granddaughters on some of these kinds of excursions
where you're doing the business of the nation to prepare them to be
president?
   A. Yeah. When they get older than about 3, I will do that,
because now _ I know, now don't you say it, I'll say it _ Jenna and
Barbara are about 7, but that's a little young to go fishing in
Jackson Hole with their grandfather and put up with Marlin Fitzwater
and all of these people. I mean, I want them prepared for the real
world. I'm serious. I want them prepared, and I look forward to the
