<HEAD>Co-Founder of Tax Firm to Become Chairman; Son to Be President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Henry Bloch, 66, a co-founder of the tax
preparation company H&amp;R Block Inc., will step aside as president
Aug. 1, becoming chairman, the company announced.
   That position has been vacant since Bloch's brother and
co-founder, Richard A. Bloch, retired in 1982, the company said
Monday.
   Henry Bloch's son, Thomas, 35, will become president and chief
operating officer. He joined the company in 1976 and for the last
year has been executive vice president.
   Jerome B. Grossman, 69, who has been chief operating officer and
senior executive vice president, will become vice chairman, a new
position.
   H&amp;R Block, the nation's largest income tax preparer, was founded
in 1955. Its subsidiaries include CompuServe Inc., Personnel Pool of
America Inc. and Path Management Industries Inc.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
